# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VetInSilico Hub — environment variables example
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env.local for local development.
# In production (GitHub Pages) — variables are NOT used: the HF token
# is provided by the user via the in-app ML settings dialog (🤖 in header).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# HuggingFace access token (optional, only for ML features).
#
# How to get one:
#   1. Create a free account at https://huggingface.co/join
#   2. Go to https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
#   3. Click "New token" → type "Read" (sufficient) → name it "vet-insilico"
#   4. Copy the token (starts with "hf_...")
#   5. Paste it below OR use the in-app 🤖 button (header → settings).
#
# Token is stored only in browser localStorage. It's sent ONLY to
# https://router.huggingface.co for inference requests.
#
# Free tier: HF gives ~$0.50 of free inference credits.
# At Qwen-Coder-3B pricing ($0.01/$0.03 per 1K tokens), that's enough
# for ~50 ML analyses. ESM-2 (protein) is free.
#
HF_TOKEN=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Build-time config (optional)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Next.js static export. Default is /vet-insilico for GitHub Pages.
# Override for custom domain deployment.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_PATH=/vet-insilico
